description:
On the E. edge of big tomb.
[plan]
[plan]
In a pit in the gebel a vault of bricks
The tomb was plundered through a hole in the roof. Skulls of a young woman & child. Objects in rubbish. Built of very large bricks coated, with mud.
Edward R. Ayrton.

description:

At the throat were

5 carnelian spherical beads
Many very small bl. glaze beads forming a single string.
